goals.question: What is the most common cuisine type in the University District?
goals.visualization: bar chart of cuisine type frequency
goals.rationale: This helps identify the dominant cuisine type in the area and can inform business decisions for new restaurants.

goals.question: What is the distribution of restaurant locations in the University District?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of latitude and longitude
goals.rationale: This helps identify any clustering or patterns in restaurant locations and can inform decisions on where to open a new restaurant.

goals.question: What is the average rating of restaurants in the University District?
goals.rationale: This helps identify the overall quality of restaurants in the area and can inform decisions on where to dine.

goals.question: What is the relationship between cuisine type and restaurant rating in the University District?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of cuisine type and rating
goals.rationale: This helps identify which cuisine types tend to have higher ratings and can inform decisions on what type of restaurant to open.

goals.question: What is the distribution of restaurant ratings in the University District?
goals.rationale: This helps identify the overall distribution of restaurant ratings in the area and can inform decisions on where to dine.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    cuisine_type = data['key'].value_counts()
    cuisine_type.plot(kind='bar', color='green')
    plt.xlabel('Cuisine Type')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the most common cuisine type in the University District?')
    plt.axhline(y=cuisine_type.max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Max Frequency: {:.2f}'.format(cuisine_type.max()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['lat'], data['lng'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Latitude')
    plt.ylabel('Longitude')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of restaurant locations in the University District?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax = sns.boxplot(x=data['rating'], color='lightblue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Rating')
    ax.set_title('What is the average rating of restaurants in the University District?')
    ax.axvline(x=data['rating'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['rating'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['key', 'rating']]
    data = data.groupby('key').mean().reset_index()
    plt.scatter(data['key'], data['rating'])
    plt.xlabel('Cuisine Type')
    plt.ylabel('Average Rating')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between cuisine type and restaurant rating in the University District?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['rating'], bins=10, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['rating'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean Rating: {:.2f}'.format(data['rating'].mean()))
    plt.xlabel('Rating')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of restaurant ratings in the University District?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
